parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to premature wear, damage, or even engine failure, which can result in costly repairs, safety risks, and emotional distress.
symptoms: The temperature gauge registers high temperatures (3/4 or hotter) consistently
regardless of driving conditions
and the vehicle may experience overheating issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire/Rim Separation and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden separation of the tire from the rim can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side
the vehicle vibrates or shakes
the tire pressure monitoring system (TPMS) warning light illuminates
the tire comes completely off the rim
loss of control of the vehicle
accidents
and rollovers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the bolts that hold the brake rotor on can cause the rotor to become loose, leading to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Unusual noises or vibrations when applying the brakes
spongy brake pedal
brake rotor wobbling or loose
brake failure
or warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the front axle can cause a loss of steering and control, leading to accidents, injuries, and potentially fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loss of steering
loss of control
loud noise or vibration from the front axle
inability to steer the vehicle
vehicle pulling to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to suddenly and unexpectedly accelerate, potentially leading to accidents, loss of control, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without input from the driver
the throttle opens to an unintended position
the vehicle accelerates rapidly without warning
the vehicle's speed increases unexpectedly.
